text: Gatcombe is a village and civil parishEnglish Parishes & Welsh Communities N&C; 2004 on the Isle of Wight. It is four kilometres from Newport in the centre of the island. St. Olave's Church is a Gatcombe church dedicated in 1292, serving as chapel to Gatcombe Manor. The Gatcombe parish was established in 1560. A carved wooden effigy of Edward Estur, a local knight who fought in the Crusades, is in the church. ==References== Category:Villages on the Isle of Wight
